1. Senior DevOps Engineer

Experience Required: 5+ years

Key Responsibilities:
	•	Develop and maintain CI/CD pipelines using GitHub Actions, Jenkins, or similar tools.
	•	Automate infrastructure provisioning and configuration management using Terraform, Ansible, and Helm.
	•	Implement and optimize Kubernetes workloads, ensuring high availability and scalability.
	•	Develop automation scripts in Python, Java, or JavaScript for infrastructure and operational tasks.
	•	Lead observability initiatives using Prometheus, Grafana, Loki, and OpenTelemetry.
	•	Manage cloud-based environments (AWS, Azure, or GCP), optimizing cost and performance.
	•	Implement GitOps practices with ArgoCD or FluxCD for automated deployments.
	•	Ensure security best practices in DevOps workflows, including vulnerability scanning and compliance automation.
	•	Mentor junior DevOps engineers and contribute to DevOps best practices.

Preferred Certifications:
	•	Certified Kubernetes Administrator (CKA)
	•	AWS Certified DevOps Engineer – Professional or Azure DevOps Engineer Expert
	•	HashiCorp Certified: Terraform Associate
	•	Certified Observability Practitioner (if applicable)

⸻

2. DevOps Engineers (Mid-Level)

Experience Required: 3+ years

Key Responsibilities:
	•	Manage and deploy containerized applications using Kubernetes.
	•	Implement GitOps workflows using ArgoCD or FluxCD.
	•	Develop and maintain Helm charts for application deployment.
	•	Set up and maintain observability solutions (Prometheus, Grafana, Loki, OpenTelemetry).
	•	Automate infrastructure provisioning using Terraform and Ansible.
	•	Manage CI/CD pipelines for continuous integration and deployment.
	•	Monitor system performance, troubleshoot issues, and optimize resource utilization.
	•	Work with developers to ensure a seamless development-to-production pipeline.

Preferred Certifications:
	•	Certified Kubernetes Administrator (CKA)
	•	AWS Certified Solutions Architect – Associate or Google Cloud Professional DevOps Engineer
	•	Certified ArgoCD Associate (if available)
	•	Linux Foundation Certified System Administrator (LFCS)
